We celebrated Lucy's 4th birthday yesterday with a little family party in the yard. I was very relieved that the rain held off until the evening! It's hard to believe that she is already 4 years old, but she has grown so much over the past year. She is confident and kind and so outgoing. I was a super shy/anxious kid, so it is amazing to me to see her live her life without much worry or self-consciousness. I'm a bit jealous. Lol. She is just a really wonderful little human, and we love her so much. 🩷

I was so tired by the time I finished this on Saturday night, but I had a lot of fun making this cake for my daughter’s birthday. And she loved it, which is the most important thing. 🩷

It's the last day of school for us today, and I am feeling so grateful to all the teachers and school staff who made Lucy's first year of Pre-K so wonderful. And to all the other teachers who did the same thing for other children. Our education system is chronically underfunded by the government, which makes their jobs so, so much harder. But they still show up and put so much love into what they do. Thank you, teachers and school staff! We appreciate you so much. I hope everyone has a lovely summer. 🩷
The first year of Pre-K is over, and she has grown so much, in so many ways. 🥲🩷

Lucy asked me if there was school yesterday, so I guess I had better think up some fun activities for the summer to get us all through. 🤣 We go to the zoo a lot, and we will try out some different playgrounds/splash parks. Hit me up with your favorite summer activities for small children!

I was hoping to make a few back-to-school sets this year, but I've been dealing with an injury for the past few weeks that sadly makes working impossible. I know it doesn't really matter in the grand scheme of things, but I am SO sad that I can't make cookies for my daughter’s 1st day next week. I printed new cookie cutters and planned my designs, but it just hasn't worked out. So I will just save them for next year. And I know that she will be so happy just to go to school again, but I can't help feeling like I am disappointing her. Mom guilt is no joke. But I hope everyone has had a lovely summer, and has a wonderful 1st week back to school. 🩷🩷
Lucy starts her 2nd year of Pre-K today, and she is SO excited. 🩷

I wish I could be attending the counter-protest today. All kids deserve to have school be a safe place where they can be themselves. Sending love to all the 2SLGBTQIA+ kids and families in our community. You are valued and loved. 🏳️‍🌈🏳️‍⚧️

We went to the beautiful @robertsonvalleyfarm this morning for our annual Pumpkin Day. One of Lucy's favorite days of the year! She was SO happy. Owen wandered around, touching all of the pumpkins, and saying 'pumpkin  patch' over and over. Lol. They had so much fun! It is such a gorgeous place to visit. 🧡

Happy Thanksgiving! I hope everyone is having a lovely day.🩷

I wasn't able to make cookies this year, so here are some from a few years ago. I've been having less pain from my herniated cervical disc this past week, so I am cautiously optimistic that I might be able to make a few cookies for Halloween. :)

I was able to make cookies for the first time in almost 3 months, and it went very slowly, but mostly okay. 😅 I'm waiting to see if my neck/arm feel okay next week, but I'm hoping to make a few sets for a small flash sale before Halloween. 🧡

EDIT: Auction is now closed. $300 will be donated to the Palestine Children's Relief Fund. ❤️

AUCTION FOR GAZA: I'm offering 2 sets of 1 dozen custom cookies (1 on Facebook, 1 on Instagram). The cookies can be for any date in 2024. Bidding will be open until Nov. 1st at noon. All funds will be donated to the Palestine Children's Relief Fund. Just comment on this post to bid. 

My heart has been so heavy every day for the past few weeks. The loss of life in Israel was heartbreaking, and seeing the devastation and mass deaths in Gaza is just horrific. Seeing that parents in Gaza are writing their children's names on their arms in case they are killed or buried in rubble is something that I think will stick with me forever. That is why I chose this design for a cookie. So many children are dying, and I can't wrap my brain around how we are just watching it happen.

I am thinking of everyone who is hurting right now. There is so much pain, grief, and trauma, and the rise in antisemitism and Islamophobia is frightening. If you haven't already contacted your government representatives to demand a ceasefire, please do. 🩷
.
.
#ceasefirenow #freepalestine #gaza

I'm finishing up my holiday cookie designs today, so I will hopefully get all the options posted tomorrow! I'm just waiting to hear back about my husband's work schedule before decide on the pickup dates. :)

Hi friends, I apologize for not getting the holiday cookie options posted this weekend. My family and I are currently sick with our first Covid infection, so I will try to update everyone once we are feeling better and testing negative. I am hoping that I will still be able to make cookies in December, but I also know that rest after infection is important to help prevent Long Covid (and resting with 2 small children is easier said than done,). I worked hard on getting the designs ready, so I will be a bit crushed if it doesn't work out. But I will be sure to let everyone know once I have a plan. Thanks so much for all the support, as always. 🩷🩷

I promise I have not forgotten about holiday cookies, but I'm almost at 2 weeks of this Covid infection, and I'm still quite sick. I'm hoping to open up booking in the next week, but I am going to be really limiting the number of orders. I'm feeling frustrated and disappointed, but also exhausted.

Shortly after my son was born, I developed an autoimmune issue that made my hands swollen and painful at times. It hadn't happened in 2 years, and then as soon as I got Covid, it started again. I was already at a much higher risk for developing other autoimmune diseases, and having a Covid infection heightens that risk exponentially (not to mention the increased risk of heart attack, stroke, blood clots, etc). All that to say, I wish that people took this more seriously. Even if all this infection does is affect my hands, that still very much affects my quality of life and ability to work. Remember when we were all in this together? I miss those days. 

Anyway, I will update everyone on booking info as soon as I can. Stay safe. 🩷
All of the holiday cookie options are now posted on my FB page (link in bio). Booking will open on Sunday at 1:00. :)

Just a reminder that booking for holiday cookies opens at 1pm today! I am moving a little slower than usual, so it might take me some time to get through the emails. But I will get back to everyone as soon as I can! :)

I used cutters from @peachesanddream.ca adorable mini advent set for the pencil toppers. ❤️

December 17th pickup date is FULL. Still a few spots open on the 23rd!

I am still making my way through emails, so don't worry if I haven't responded yet! :)

December feels like such a hard month every year, but this one feels even heavier with everything happening in the world. My own grief feels so much more pervasive around the holidays, and I try to remind myself that grief and gratitude can be companions. And I am truly grateful, now perhaps more than ever, that I get to watch my kids experience the joy of the holidays, safe and warm in our home. I aim to never take that for granted again. Decorating the tree always makes me kind of sad, but it made the kids SO happy, and that makes it all a bit easier. 🩷
